WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.250 --> 00:00:04.200
Speaker 1: Broadway?

00:00:04.200 --> 00:00:06.150
Broadway: Oh, man.

00:00:06.150 --> 00:00:11.099
Speaker 1: I hear it all the time, man.

00:00:11.099 --> 00:00:12.670
Kids ask me, they say, "Hey, man.

00:00:12.670 --> 00:00:15.420
I want to play just like Michael Jordan."

00:00:15.420 --> 00:00:16.500
So I had an answer for them.

00:00:16.500 --> 00:00:17.500
Broadway: What's the answer?

00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:18.640
Speaker 1: I told them, "You know what?

00:00:18.640 --> 00:00:20.590
Just go out there and stick your tongue out
like this.

00:00:20.590 --> 00:00:21.590
Alright?"

00:00:21.590 --> 00:00:23.630
"Then you'll be like Michael."

00:00:23.630 --> 00:00:24.630
Right?

00:00:24.630 --> 00:00:25.660
Broadway: No, man.

00:00:25.660 --> 00:00:26.660
Michael's the G.O.A.T.

00:00:26.660 --> 00:00:27.660
Speaker 1: He is, man.

00:00:27.660 --> 00:00:28.660
He is the -

00:00:28.660 --> 00:00:29.660
Broadway: Greatest Of All Time.

00:00:29.660 --> 00:00:30.660
Speaker 1: Greatest Of All Time.

00:00:30.660 --> 00:00:31.660
I like it.

00:00:31.660 --> 00:00:32.660
Yes, sir.

00:00:32.660 --> 00:00:34.890
Broadway: But, let's just say we can teach
the people how Michael Jordan plays.

00:00:34.890 --> 00:00:35.890
Speaker 1: Right.

00:00:35.890 --> 00:00:39.810
Broadway: Teach them some of his moves and
maybe they can pattern their game after him.

00:00:39.810 --> 00:00:40.810
There's only one Michael.

00:00:40.810 --> 00:00:41.810
Speaker 1: There sure is.

00:00:41.810 --> 00:00:42.810
Broadway: There's only one greatest.

00:00:42.810 --> 00:00:44.190
Speaker 1: Lots of work in the gym.

00:00:44.190 --> 00:00:48.579
Broadway: So, you know, I don't want to be
confused with saying, "I'm as good as Michael."

00:00:48.579 --> 00:00:49.579
Speaker 1: No, no, no, no.

00:00:49.579 --> 00:00:51.110
Broadway: But, we're going to teach them the
way Michael plays.

00:00:51.110 --> 00:00:52.110
Speaker 1: OK.

00:00:52.110 --> 00:00:53.110
Sounds good.

00:00:53.110 --> 00:00:54.149
Broadway: So we'll take two of Michael's signature
moves -

00:00:54.149 --> 00:00:55.149
Speaker 1: OK.

00:00:55.149 --> 00:00:56.149
Broadway: Break them down.

00:00:56.149 --> 00:00:57.149
Speaker 1: Alright.

00:00:57.149 --> 00:00:58.149
Broadway: And show the kids how to practice
-

00:00:58.149 --> 00:00:59.149
Speaker 1: OK.

00:00:59.149 --> 00:01:00.149
I'll be Craig Ehlo.

00:01:00.149 --> 00:01:01.149
Broadway: Being like Mike.

00:01:01.149 --> 00:01:02.149
Speaker 1: And you'll be Michael Jordan.

00:01:02.149 --> 00:01:03.149
Broadway: Oh!

00:01:03.149 --> 00:01:04.149
You know what?

00:01:04.149 --> 00:01:05.149
That's good.

00:01:05.149 --> 00:01:06.149
Speaker 1: Now, Broadway, you told me that
tongue is not the only thing I need to do.

00:01:06.149 --> 00:01:09.580
I need to get in the gym, I need to work hard
and I got to perfect my game if I even want

00:01:09.580 --> 00:01:11.970
to come close to playing like the greatest
of all time.

00:01:11.970 --> 00:01:12.970
Broadway: Yep.

00:01:12.970 --> 00:01:13.970
Speaker 1: Correct?

00:01:13.970 --> 00:01:16.500
